castAddBody.text: Put these noggles on and now Twitter looks different... weird.

Been reworking Prop 371 (https://nounsagora.com/proposals/371) to get it back onchain for another vote, and while the asks and deliverables are basically staying the same - with some more nuanced language around earning a Noun - I've taken a bit of time this week to jam on the creative to flesh out the prop.

The idea for the prop has always been to capture stills from an as-of-now non-existent television series.

But I figured, the best way to know what those images should be was to know what the show is.

So I kind of accidentally wrote a 'scriptment' of a pilot episode.

Let me caveat that this is just a couple quick sessions of writing, so it's rough and normally I wouldn't share creative like this at such an early stage.

But I figure, this is a unique way to fund a project so I'll build in public a little and be more open and less polished (for now!).

If you're curious about the idea, check it out here: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1sNWmF0Lhlqe7bRMHra9EKHyoLSPr3B1CDIwSJJw8sTs/edit?usp=sharing

I'm always open to feedback, so feel free to drop comments here, but for now I gotta rewrite this prop and get it back up!

There's been talk of gifting nouns as retro rewards and potentially having some sort of vesting on them so that people don't turn around and immediately sell. 

What if every noun auctioned had vesting built in (set time period)? Then everyone is coming in long-ish term, but can sell/fork later if they want.

This in combo with the burn leads to aligned incentives across the board. Things have to be done to increase meme value and thus value of nouns or eth goes bye bye. Additionally, offramp is cascaded.

Goes back to my college analogy. You don't get the paper until you get the education üòÖ

The üî• isn't there to recklessly burn eth.

The üî• is there to light a fire under everyone so that it's not burned.

100% agree with you that props are the most important thing to make the experiment work. 

Good props do three things, spread the meme to more people, bring more people to the meme and fund the meme cycle. 

The best way to get more people involved is by showing them what cool things can happen thanks to Nouns.

I think burn helps encourage everybody who wants to see this experiment work to dream up big ideas, tap their network, and in general explain Nouns to more people so that more of the props you're talking about come in.

People do fan art because they LOVE the characters, not the brands. Right now Nouns are cute, but it's still a brand and I think they need a personality and a story for people to truly fall in love in that way.

I always reference a24 as a brand people want to work with bc they are 1) cool, 2) elevate and respect the creative talent they work with and 3) have created a niche making 'a24 films', which is now a thing people get. 

Nouns should be where creatives make nounish things, but first people need to know what that means.

Nouns is 2 years old. A24 (just to use my own example) was founded in 2012. This stuff doesn't happen overnight. 

Just gotta keep making great stuff and defining what it means to be nounish.
